notes.text: a Within 42 days of ALXN1840 administration.
b Participants will be admitted to the clinical research unit (CRU) at least 10 hours prior to enrollment.
c At the CRU's discretion, participants may remain in the CRU or be readmitted on Day 22.
d Unscheduled study visits may occur at any time during the study.
e Participants are required to return to the CRU Day 54+/-2.
f Discharge from the unit may occur after completion of all procedures on Day 9 and on Day 40.
g A single outpatient visit or phone call and safety laboratory assessment should occur between Day 14 and Day 18.
h If needed to confirm menopause.
i Parameters include age and sex.
j Wilson disease history will include diagnosis date, method of diagnosis, etc.
k A full physical examination will be performed at Screening, at check-in, and at the End of Study.
l Height at screening only.
m Study intervention will be administered after an overnight fast.
n During the outpatient period, participants will use SMS text messaging to confirm administration.
o Blood sampling for PK/PD will occur before ALXN1840 administration.
p PK/PD collection will include timepoints described in the schedule of PK/PD assessment.
q Samples for serum chemistry will be obtained following a fast of at least 8 hours.
r Laboratory assessment including chemistry, hematology, and coagulation parameters should be performed on Days -8, -1, 8, 23, and 28 only.
s Menstruation check is for women only.
t A single 15 mL serum sample will be retained for evaluation in the event of an unexpected safety finding.
u Vital signs measurements and ECGs should be performed predose.
v Copper- and molybdenum-controlled diet will be initiated after registration/inclusion.
w For each input/output balance period, 24-hour urine samples are to be collected.
x For fecal samples, each individual sample will be independently collected.
